annotationA: Protein kinase, cAMP-dependent, catalytic subunit 1 is a serine/threonine kinase that contributes to axis specification, rhythmic behavior and synaptic transmission
annotationB: Casein kinase II subunit alpha; Casein kinases are operationally defined by their preferential utilization of acidic proteins such as caseins as substrates. The alpha chain contains the catalytic site. May participate in Wnt signaling
